P_HTM[923]="*10. Vassūpanāyikasuttaṃ**98*";
P_HTM[924]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, bālā.**“Mendicants, there are two fools.*";
P_HTM[925]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[926]="*Yo ca anāgataṃ bhāraṃ vahati, yo ca āgataṃ bhāraṃ na vahati.**One who takes responsibility for what has not come to pass, and one who doesn’t take responsibility for what has come to pass.*";
P_HTM[927]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve bālā”ti.**These are the two fools.”*";
P_HTM[928]="*99**99*";
P_HTM[929]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, paṇḍitā.**“There are two who are astute.*";
P_HTM[930]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[931]="*Yo ca anāgataṃ bhāraṃ na vahati, yo ca āgataṃ bhāraṃ vahati.**One who doesn’t take responsibility for what has not come to pass, and one who does take responsibility for what has come to pass.*";
P_HTM[932]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve paṇḍitā”ti.**These are the two who are astute.”*";
P_HTM[933]="*100**100*";
P_HTM[934]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, bālā.**“Mendicants, there are two fools.*";
P_HTM[935]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[936]="*Yo ca akappiye kappiyasaññī, yo ca kappiye akappiyasaññī.**One who perceives what is unallowable as allowable, and one who perceives what is allowable as unallowable.*";
P_HTM[937]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve bālā”ti.**These are the two fools.”*";
