P_HTM[1023]="*Bālavaggo pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[1024]="*Dutiyo paṇṇāsako samatto.* **";
P_HTM[1025]="*14. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**118*";
P_HTM[1026]="*“Dvemā, bhikkhave, āsā duppajahā.**“These two hopes are hard to give up.*";
P_HTM[1027]="*Katamā dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1028]="*Lābhāsā ca jīvitāsā ca.**The hope for wealth and the hope for long life.*";
P_HTM[1029]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, dve āsā duppajahā”ti.**These are two hopes that are hard to give up.”*";
P_HTM[1030]="*119**119*";
P_HTM[1031]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, puggalā dullabhā lokasmiṃ.**“These two people are rare in the world.*";
P_HTM[1032]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1033]="*Yo ca pubbakārī, yo ca kataññū katavedī.**One who takes the initiative, and one who is grateful and thankful.*";
P_HTM[1034]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve puggalā dullabhā lokasmin”ti.**These are the two people who are rare in the world.”*";
P_HTM[1035]="*120**120*";
P_HTM[1036]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, puggalā dullabhā lokasmiṃ.**“These two people are rare in the world.*";
P_HTM[1037]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1038]="*Titto ca tappetā ca.**One who is satisfied, and one who satisfies others.*";
P_HTM[1039]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve puggalā dullabhā lokasmin”ti.**These are the two people who are rare in the world.”*";
P_HTM[1040]="*121**121*";
P_HTM[1041]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, puggalā duttappayā.**“These two people are hard to satisfy in the world.*";
P_HTM[1042]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1043]="*Yo ca laddhaṃ laddhaṃ nikkhipati, yo ca laddhaṃ laddhaṃ vissajjeti.**One who continually hoards wealth, and one who continually wastes wealth.*";
P_HTM[1044]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve puggalā duttappayā”ti.**These are the two people who are hard to satisfy in the world.”*";
P_HTM[1045]="*122**122*";
P_HTM[1046]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, puggalā sutappayā.**“These two people are easy to satisfy in the world.*";
P_HTM[1047]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1048]="*Yo ca laddhaṃ laddhaṃ na nikkhipati, yo ca laddhaṃ laddhaṃ na vissajjeti.**One who does not continually hoard wealth, and one who does not continually waste wealth.*";
P_HTM[1049]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve puggalā sutappayā”ti.**These are the two people who are easy to satisfy in the world.”*";
P_HTM[1050]="*123**123*";
P_HTM[1051]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, paccayā rāgassa uppādāya.**“There are two conditions for the arising of greed.*";
P_HTM[1052]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1053]="*Subhanimittañca ayoniso ca manasikāro.**The feature of beauty and improper attention.*";
P_HTM[1054]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve paccayā rāgassa uppādāyā”ti.**These are the two conditions for the arising of greed.”*";
P_HTM[1055]="*124**124*";
P_HTM[1056]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, paccayā dosassa uppādāya.**“There are two conditions for the arising of hate.*";
P_HTM[1057]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1058]="*Paṭighanimittañca ayoniso ca manasikāro.**The feature of harshness and improper attention.*";
P_HTM[1059]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve paccayā dosassa uppādāyā”ti.**These are the two conditions for the arising of hate.”*";
P_HTM[1060]="*125**125*";
P_HTM[1061]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, paccayā micchādiṭṭhiyā uppādāya.**“There are two conditions for the arising of wrong view.*";
P_HTM[1062]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1063]="*Parato ca ghoso ayoniso ca manasikāro.**The words of another and improper attention.*";
P_HTM[1064]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve paccayā micchādiṭṭhiyā uppādāyā”ti.**These are the two conditions for the arising of wrong view.”*";
P_HTM[1065]="*126**126*";
P_HTM[1066]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, paccayā sammādiṭṭhiyā uppādāya.**“There are two conditions for the arising of right view.*";
P_HTM[1067]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1068]="*Parato ca ghoso, yoniso ca manasikāro.**The words of another and proper attention.*";
P_HTM[1069]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve paccayā sammādiṭṭhiyā uppādāyā”ti.**These are the two conditions for the arising of right view.”*";
P_HTM[1070]="*127**127*";
P_HTM[1071]="*“Dvemā, bhikkhave, āpattiyo.**“There are these two offenses.*";
P_HTM[1072]="*Katamā dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1073]="*Lahukā ca āpatti, garukā ca āpatti.**A light offense and a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[1074]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, dve āpattiyo”ti.**These are the two offenses.”*";
P_HTM[1075]="*128**128*";
P_HTM[1076]="*“Dvemā, bhikkhave, āpattiyo.**“There are these two offenses.*";
P_HTM[1077]="*Katamā dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1078]="*Duṭṭhullā ca āpatti, aduṭṭhullā ca āpatti.**An offense with corrupt intention and an offense without corrupt intention.*";
P_HTM[1079]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, dve āpattiyo”ti.**These are the two offenses.”*";
P_HTM[1080]="*129**129*";
P_HTM[1081]="*“Dvemā, bhikkhave, āpattiyo.**“There are these two offenses.*";
P_HTM[1082]="*Katamā dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1083]="*Sāvasesā ca āpatti, anavasesā ca āpatti.**An offense requiring rehabilitation and an offense not requiring rehabilitation.*";
P_HTM[1084]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, dve āpattiyo”ti.**These are the two offenses.”*";
P_HTM[1085]="*Āsāduppajahavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[1086]="*14. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**130*";
P_HTM[1087]="*“Saddho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ sammā āyācamāno āyāceyya:**“A faithful monk would rightly aspire:*";
P_HTM[1088]="*‘tādiso homi yādisā sāriputtamoggallānā’ti.**‘May I be like Sāriputta and Moggallāna!’*";
P_HTM[1089]="*Esā, bhikkhave, tulā etaṃ pamāṇaṃ mama sāvakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ yadidaṃ sāriputtamoggallānā”ti.**These are a standard and a measure for my monk disciples, that is, Sāriputta and Moggallāna.”*";
P_HTM[1090]="*131**131*";
P_HTM[1091]="*“Saddhā, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī evaṃ sammā āyācamānā āyāceyya:**“A faithful nun would rightly aspire:*";
P_HTM[1092]="*‘tādisī homi yādisī khemā ca bhikkhunī uppalavaṇṇā cā’ti.**‘May I be like the nuns Khemā and Uppalavaṇṇā!’*";
P_HTM[1093]="*Esā, bhikkhave, tulā etaṃ pamāṇaṃ mama sāvikānaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ yadidaṃ khemā ca bhikkhunī uppalavaṇṇā cā”ti.**These are a standard and a measure for my nun disciples, that is, the nuns Khemā and Uppalavaṇṇā.”*";
P_HTM[1094]="*132**132*";
P_HTM[1095]="*“Saddho, bhikkhave, upāsako evaṃ sammā āyācamāno āyāceyya:**“A faithful layman would rightly aspire:*";
P_HTM[1096]="*‘tādiso homi yādiso citto ca gahapati hatthako ca āḷavako’ti.**‘May I be like the householder Citta and Hatthaka of Aḷavī!’*";
P_HTM[1097]="*Esā, bhikkhave, tulā etaṃ pamāṇaṃ mama sāvakānaṃ upāsakānaṃ yadidaṃ citto ca gahapati hatthako ca āḷavako”ti.**These are a standard and a measure for my male lay followers, that is, the householder Citta and Hatthaka of Aḷavī.”*";
P_HTM[1098]="*133**133*";
P_HTM[1099]="*“Saddhā, bhikkhave, upāsikā evaṃ sammā āyācamānā āyāceyya:**“A faithful laywoman would rightly aspire:*";
P_HTM[1100]="*‘tādisī homi yādisī khujjuttarā ca upāsikā veḷukaṇḍakiyā ca nandamātā’ti.**‘May I be like the laywomen Khujjuttarā and Veḷukaṇṭakī, Nanda’s mother!’*";
P_HTM[1101]="*Esā, bhikkhave, tulā etaṃ pamāṇaṃ mama sāvikānaṃ upāsikānaṃ yadidaṃ khujjuttarā ca upāsikā veḷukaṇḍakiyā ca nandamātā”ti.**These are a standard and a measure for my female lay disciples, that is, the laywomen Khujjuttarā and Veḷukaṇṭakī, Nanda’s mother.”*";
P_HTM[1102]="*134**134*";
P_HTM[1103]="*“Dvīhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**“When a foolish, incompetent bad person has two qualities they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[1104]="*Katamehi dvīhi?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1105]="*Ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**Without examining or scrutinizing, they praise those deserving of criticism*";
P_HTM[1106]="*ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.**and they criticize those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[1107]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dvīhi dhammehi samannāgato bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavatīti.**When a foolish, incompetent bad person has these two qualities they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[1108]="*Dvīhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca puññaṃ pasavati.**When an astute, competent good person has two qualities they keep themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much merit.*";
P_HTM[1109]="*Katamehi dvīhi?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1110]="*Anuvicca pariyogāhetvā avaṇṇārahassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,**After examining and scrutinizing, they criticize those deserving of criticism*";
P_HTM[1111]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā vaṇṇārahassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.**and they praise those deserving of praise.*";
P_HTM[1112]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dvīhi dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca puññaṃ pasavatī”ti.**When an astute, competent good person has these two qualities they keep themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much merit.”*";
P_HTM[1113]="*135**135*";
P_HTM[1114]="*“Dvīhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**“When a foolish, incompetent bad person has two qualities they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[1115]="*Katamehi dvīhi?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1116]="*Ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā appasādanīye ṭhāne pasādaṃ upadaṃseti,**Without examining or scrutinizing, they arouse faith in things that are dubious,*";
P_HTM[1117]="*ananuvicca apariyogāhetvā pasādanīye ṭhāne appasādaṃ upadaṃseti.**and they don’t arouse faith in things that are inspiring.*";
P_HTM[1118]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dvīhi dhammehi samannāgato bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavatīti.**When a foolish, incompetent bad person has these two qualities they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[1119]="*Dvīhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca puññaṃ pasavati.**When an astute, competent good person has two qualities they keep themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much merit.*";
P_HTM[1120]="*Katamehi dvīhi?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1121]="*Anuvicca pariyogāhetvā appasādanīye ṭhāne appasādaṃ upadaṃseti,**After examining or scrutinizing, they don’t arouse faith in things that are dubious,*";
P_HTM[1122]="*anuvicca pariyogāhetvā pasādanīye ṭhāne pasādaṃ upadaṃseti.**and they do arouse faith in things that are inspiring.*";
P_HTM[1123]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dvīhi dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca puññaṃ pasavatī”ti.**When an astute, competent good person has these two qualities they keep themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much merit.”*";
P_HTM[1124]="*136**136*";
P_HTM[1125]="*“Dvīsu, bhikkhave, micchāpaṭipajjamāno bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**“When a foolish, incompetent bad person acts wrongly toward two people they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[1126]="*Katamesu dvīsu?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1127]="*Mātari ca pitari ca.**Mother and father.*";
P_HTM[1128]="*Imesu kho, bhikkhave, dvīsu micchāpaṭipajjamāno bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavatīti.**When a foolish, incompetent bad person acts wrongly toward these two people they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[1129]="*Dvīsu, bhikkhave, sammāpaṭipajjamāno paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca puññaṃ pasavati.**When an astute, competent good person acts rightly toward two people they keep themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much merit.*";
P_HTM[1130]="*Katamesu dvīsu?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1131]="*Mātari ca pitari ca.**Mother and father.*";
P_HTM[1132]="*Imesu kho, bhikkhave, dvīsu sammāpaṭipajjamāno paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca puññaṃ pasavatī”ti.**When an astute, competent good person acts rightly toward these two people they keep themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much merit.”*";
P_HTM[1133]="*137**137*";
P_HTM[1134]="*“Dvīsu, bhikkhave, micchāpaṭipajjamāno bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati.**“When a foolish, incompetent bad person acts wrongly toward two people they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[1135]="*Katamesu dvīsu?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1136]="*Tathāgate ca tathāgatasāvake ca.**The Realized One and a disciple of the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[1137]="*Imesu kho, bhikkhave, micchāpaṭipajjamāno bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavatīti.**When a foolish, incompetent bad person acts wrongly toward these people they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma.*";
P_HTM[1138]="*Dvīsu, bhikkhave, sammāpaṭipajjamāno paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca puññaṃ pasavati.**When an astute, competent good person acts rightly toward two people they keep themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much merit.*";
P_HTM[1139]="*Katamesu dvīsu?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1140]="*Tathāgate ca tathāgatasāvake ca.**The Realized One and a disciple of the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[1141]="*Imesu kho, bhikkhave, dvīsu sammāpaṭipajjamāno paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo ca viññūnaṃ, bahuñca puññaṃ pasavatī”ti.**When an astute, competent good person acts rightly toward these two people they keep themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much merit.”*";
P_HTM[1142]="*138**138*";
P_HTM[1143]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, dhammā.**“There are these two things.*";
P_HTM[1144]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1145]="*Sacittavodānañca na ca kiñci loke upādiyati.**Cleaning your own mind, and not grasping at anything in the world.*";
P_HTM[1146]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve dhammā”ti.**These are the two things.”*";
P_HTM[1147]="*139**139*";
P_HTM[1148]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, dhammā.**“There are these two things.*";
P_HTM[1149]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1150]="*Kodho ca upanāho ca.**Anger and hostility.*";
P_HTM[1151]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve dhammā”ti.**These are the two things.”*";
P_HTM[1152]="*140**140*";
P_HTM[1153]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, dhammā.**“There are these two things.*";
P_HTM[1154]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1155]="*Kodhavinayo ca upanāhavinayo ca.**Dispelling anger and dispelling hostility.*";
P_HTM[1156]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve dhammā”ti.**These are the two things.”*";
P_HTM[1157]="*Āyācanavaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[1158]="*14. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**141*";
P_HTM[1159]="*“Dvemāni, bhikkhave, dānāni.**“There are these two gifts.*";
P_HTM[1160]="*Katamāni dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1161]="*Āmisadānañca dhammadānañca.**A gift of material things and a gift of the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1162]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, dve dānāni.**These are the two gifts.*";
P_HTM[1163]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ dānānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammadānan”ti.**The better of these two gifts is the gift of the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1164]="*142**142*";
P_HTM[1165]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, yāgā.**“There are these two offerings.*";
P_HTM[1166]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1167]="*Āmisayāgo ca dhammayāgo ca.**An offering of material things and an offering of the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1168]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve yāgā.**These are the two offerings.*";
P_HTM[1169]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ yāgānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammayāgo”ti.**The better of these two offerings is an offering of the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1170]="*143**143*";
P_HTM[1171]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, cāgā.**“There are these two acts of generosity.*";
P_HTM[1172]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1173]="*Āmisacāgo ca dhammacāgo ca.**Generosity with material things and generosity with the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1174]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve cāgā.**These are the two acts of generosity.*";
P_HTM[1175]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ cāgānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammacāgo”ti.**The better of these two acts of generosity is generosity with the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1176]="*144**144*";
P_HTM[1177]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, pariccāgā.**“There are these two kinds of charity.*";
P_HTM[1178]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1179]="*Āmisapariccāgo ca dhammapariccāgo ca.**Charity in material things and charity in the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1180]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve pariccāgā.**These are the two kinds of charity.*";
P_HTM[1181]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ pariccāgānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammapariccāgo”ti.**The better of these two kinds of charity is a charity in the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1182]="*145**145*";
P_HTM[1183]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, bhogā.**“There are these two riches.*";
P_HTM[1184]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1185]="*Āmisabhogo ca dhammabhogo ca.**Riches in material things and riches in the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1186]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve bhogā.**These are the two riches.*";
P_HTM[1187]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ bhogānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammabhogo”ti.**The better of these two riches is riches in the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1188]="*146**146*";
P_HTM[1189]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, sambhogā.**“There are these two kinds of enjoyment.*";
P_HTM[1190]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1191]="*Āmisasambhogo ca dhammasambhogo ca.**Enjoyment of material things and enjoyment of the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1192]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve sambhogā.**These are the two kinds of enjoyment.*";
P_HTM[1193]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ sambhogānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammasambhogo”ti.**The better of these two kinds of enjoyment is the enjoyment of the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1194]="*147**147*";
P_HTM[1195]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, saṃvibhāgā.**“There are these two kinds of sharing.*";
P_HTM[1196]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1197]="*Āmisasaṃvibhāgo ca dhammasaṃvibhāgo ca.**Sharing material things and sharing the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1198]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve saṃvibhāgā.**These are the two kinds of sharing.*";
P_HTM[1199]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ saṃvibhāgānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammasaṃvibhāgo”ti.**The better of these two kinds of sharing is sharing the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1200]="*148**148*";
P_HTM[1201]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, saṅgahā.**“There are these two kinds of inclusion.*";
P_HTM[1202]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1203]="*Āmisasaṅgaho ca dhammasaṅgaho ca.**Inclusion in material things and inclusion in the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1204]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve saṅgahā.**These are the two kinds of inclusion.*";
P_HTM[1205]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ saṅgahānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammasaṅgaho”ti.**The better of these two kinds of inclusion is inclusion in the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1206]="*149**149*";
P_HTM[1207]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, anuggahā.**“There are these two kinds of support.*";
P_HTM[1208]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1209]="*Āmisānuggaho ca dhammānuggaho ca.**Support in material things and support in the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1210]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve anuggahā.**These are the two kinds of support.*";
P_HTM[1211]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ anuggahānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammānuggaho”ti.**The better of these two kinds of support is support in the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1212]="*150**150*";
P_HTM[1213]="*“Dvemā, bhikkhave, anukampā.**“There are these two kinds of sympathy.*";
P_HTM[1214]="*Katamā dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1215]="*Āmisānukampā ca dhammānukampā ca.**Sympathy in material things and sympathy in the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1216]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, dve anukampā.**These are the two kinds of sympathy.*";
P_HTM[1217]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ dvinnaṃ anukampānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammānukampā”ti.**The better of these two kinds of sympathy is sympathy in the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1218]="*Dānavaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[1219]="*14. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**151*";
P_HTM[1220]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, santhārā.**“There are these two kinds of welcome.*";
P_HTM[1221]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1222]="*Āmisasanthāro ca dhammasanthāro ca.**Welcome in material things and welcome in the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1223]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve santhārā.**These are the two kinds of welcome.*";
P_HTM[1224]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ santhārānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammasanthāro”ti.**The better of these two kinds of welcome is the welcome in the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1225]="*152**152*";
P_HTM[1226]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, paṭisanthārā.**“There are these two kinds of hospitality.*";
P_HTM[1227]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1228]="*Āmisapaṭisanthāro ca dhammapaṭisanthāro ca.**Hospitality in material things and hospitality in the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1229]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve paṭisanthārā.**These are the two kinds of hospitality.*";
P_HTM[1230]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ paṭisanthārānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammapaṭisanthāro”ti.**The better of these two kinds of hospitality is hospitality in the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1231]="*153**153*";
P_HTM[1232]="*“Dvemā, bhikkhave, esanā.**“There are these two quests.*";
P_HTM[1233]="*Katamā dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1234]="*Āmisesanā ca dhammesanā ca.**The quest for material things and the quest for the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1235]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, dve esanā.**These are the two quests.*";
P_HTM[1236]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ dvinnaṃ esanānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammesanā”ti.**The better of these two quests is the quest for the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1237]="*154**154*";
P_HTM[1238]="*“Dvemā, bhikkhave, pariyesanā.**“There are these two searches.*";
P_HTM[1239]="*Katamā dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1240]="*Āmisapariyesanā ca dhammapariyesanā ca.**The search for material things and the search for the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1241]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, dve pariyesanā.**These are the two searches.*";
P_HTM[1242]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ dvinnaṃ pariyesanānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammapariyesanā”ti.**The better of these two searches is the search for the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1243]="*155**155*";
P_HTM[1244]="*“Dvemā, bhikkhave, pariyeṭṭhiyo.**“There are these two kinds of seeking.*";
P_HTM[1245]="*Katamā dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1246]="*Āmisapariyeṭṭhi ca dhammapariyeṭṭhi ca.**Seeking for material things and seeking for the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1247]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, dve pariyeṭṭhiyo.**These are the two kinds of seeking.*";
P_HTM[1248]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ dvinnaṃ pariyeṭṭhīnaṃ yadidaṃ dhammapariyeṭṭhī”ti.**The better of these two kinds of seeking is seeking for the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1249]="*156**156*";
P_HTM[1250]="*“Dvemā, bhikkhave, pūjā.**“There are these two kinds of worship.*";
P_HTM[1251]="*Katamā dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1252]="*Āmisapūjā ca dhammapūjā ca.**Worship of material things and worship of the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1253]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, dve pūjā.**These are the two kinds of worship.*";
P_HTM[1254]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ dvinnaṃ pūjānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammapūjā”ti.**The better of these two kinds of worship is worship of the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1255]="*157**157*";
P_HTM[1256]="*“Dvemāni, bhikkhave, ātitheyyāni.**“There are these two ways of serving guests.*";
P_HTM[1257]="*Katamāni dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1258]="*Āmisātitheyyañca dhammātitheyyañca.**Serving guests with material things and serving guests with the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1259]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, dve ātitheyyāni.**These are the two ways of serving guests.*";
P_HTM[1260]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ ātitheyyānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammātitheyyan”ti.**The better of these two ways of serving guests is to serve them with the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1261]="*158**158*";
P_HTM[1262]="*“Dvemā, bhikkhave, iddhiyo.**“There are, mendicants, these two successes.*";
P_HTM[1263]="*Katamā dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1264]="*Āmisiddhi ca dhammiddhi ca.**Success in material things and success in the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1265]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, dve iddhiyo.**These are the two successes.*";
P_HTM[1266]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ dvinnaṃ iddhīnaṃ yadidaṃ dhammiddhī”ti.**The better of these two successes is success in the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1267]="*159**159*";
P_HTM[1268]="*“Dvemā, bhikkhave, vuddhiyo.**“There are, mendicants, these two kinds of growth.*";
P_HTM[1269]="*Katamā dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1270]="*Āmisavuddhi ca dhammavuddhi ca.**Growth in material things and growth in the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1271]="*Imā kho, bhikkhave, dve vuddhiyo.**These are the two kinds of growth.*";
P_HTM[1272]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ dvinnaṃ vuddhīnaṃ yadidaṃ dhammavuddhī”ti.**The better of these two kinds of growth is growth in the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1273]="*160**160*";
P_HTM[1274]="*“Dvemāni, bhikkhave, ratanāni.**“There are these two treasures.*";
P_HTM[1275]="*Katamāni dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1276]="*Āmisaratanañca dhammaratanañca.**The treasure of material things and the treasure of the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1277]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, dve ratanāni.**These are the two treasures.*";
P_HTM[1278]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ ratanānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammaratanan”ti.**The better of these two treasures is the treasure of the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1279]="*161**161*";
P_HTM[1280]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, sannicayā.**“There are these two kinds of accumulation.*";
P_HTM[1281]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1282]="*Āmisasannicayo ca dhammasannicayo ca.**Accumulation of material things and accumulation of the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1283]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve sannicayā.**These are the two kinds of accumulation.*";
P_HTM[1284]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ sannicayānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammasannicayo”ti.**The better of these two kinds of accumulation is the accumulation of the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1285]="*162**162*";
P_HTM[1286]="*“Dvemāni, bhikkhave, vepullāni.**“There are, mendicants, these two kinds of increase.*";
P_HTM[1287]="*Katamāni dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1288]="*Āmisavepullañca dhammavepullañca.**Increase in material things and increase in the teaching.*";
P_HTM[1289]="*Imāni kho, bhikkhave, dve vepullāni.**These are the two kinds of increase.*";
P_HTM[1290]="*Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ dvinnaṃ vepullānaṃ yadidaṃ dhammavepullan”ti.**The better of these two kinds of increase is increase in the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[1291]="*Santhāravaggo catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[1292]="*14. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**163*";
P_HTM[1293]="*“Dveme, bhikkhave, dhammā.**“There are these two things.*";
P_HTM[1294]="*Katame dve?**What two?*";
P_HTM[1295]="*Samāpattikusalatā ca samāpattivuṭṭhānakusalatā ca.**Skill in meditative attainments and skill in emerging from those attainments.*";
P_HTM[1296]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dve dhammā”ti.**These are the two things.”*";
